{
  "$type": "Models.Core.Simulations, Models",
  "Version": 216,
  "Name": "Simulations",
  "ResourceName": null,
  "Children": [
    {
      "$type": "Models.Memo, Models",
      "Text": "Acknowledgement: We would like to express our gratitude to Department of Primary Industries and Regional Development of Western Australia for providing dataset for setting up and validating Apsim damage functions of frost and heat event.\n \nData description: The data was collected from field trials conducted in 2017 and 2018 for the Advancing Profitable Farming Systems - Frost Risk Management project (grant number: DAW00260).  It includes trial metadata encompassing the trial locations and soil types, field management practices (sowing date, cultivar name, irrigation, and fertilization), and field measurements of crop traits including phenology, maturity biomass, grain yield, and floret sterility.\n \nDisclaimer: The creators, contributors, and distributors of the dataset shall not be held liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, or consequential damages arising from the use of the dataset, including but not limited to, inaccuracies, errors, or omissions in the data.\nUnauthorized use or dissemination of this data is prohibited without explicit permission from the Department of the Primary Industries and Regional Development of Western Australia. For further inquiries or permission requests, please contact Dr Brenton Leske(Brenton.Leske@dpird.wa.gov.au).\n \nWhen citing this dataset, please use the following reference: Biddulph T.B. (Creator) (26 June 2023). GRDC/DPIRD Frost Agronomy Trials 2017 and 2018. The Department of Primary Industries and Regional Development Western Australia. [https://github.com/APSIMInitiative/ApsimX](https://github.com/APSIMInitiative/ApsimX)\n\n\nWhen using the damage functions, please use the following reference for more information: Hu, P., He, D., Zheng, B., Whish, J., Kirkegaard, J., Bell, L., Leske, B., Chen, S., Uppal, R., Biddulph, B., Trethowan, R., Beletse, Y., Lilley, J., 2026. Event-based frost and heat damage functions improve yield predictions of APSIM canola and wheat: formulation, calibration, and evaluation. Agricultural and Forest Meteorology 386, 111239. https://doi.org/10.1016/j.agrformet.2026.111239",
      "Name": "Data Ownership Acknowledgement",
      "ResourceName": null,
      "Children": [],
      "Enabled": true,
      "ReadOnly": false
    },
